abstract: Disney reported a profit of $1.48 billion and told analysts that economic fears were not hurting theme park bookings so far.
snippet: Disney reported a profit of $1.48 billion and told analysts that economic fears were not hurting theme park bookings so far.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The Walt Disney Company, reporting a profit of $1.48 billion in its most recent quarter, told analysts that whipsawing financial markets and fears of a double-dip recession were not hurting theme park bookings — so far.

headline.main: Disney Beats Expectations, Posting 11% Rise in Profit
headline.print_headline: Disney Beats Expectations, Posting 11% Rise in Profit
